Reasoning: This paper focuses on the usage and evolution of Kotlin features in Android development, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) categories. The analysis of source code and identification of feature usage trends also involves machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical analysis (cs.SD). Additionally, the study of feature adoption and evolution can be considered a form of software maintenance and evolution (cs.MS).
